BACKGROUND:
PACT v0.2 is Invoica's mandate protocol. When an AI agent calls Invoica, it can attach a signed X-Pact-Mandate header that authorises the payment (caps spend, scopes actions, sets expiry). The server-side pact-verify.ts already handles verification — but there is NO published npm package for agents to CREATE mandates. That's what this task builds.

The comment in pact-verify.ts says: "Does NOT import @godman-protocols/pact (not on npm — server cannot install it)." This task closes that gap by publishing @invoica/pact.

Scope of v1.0.0 (mandate layer only — session layer comes in v1.1.0):
- issueMandate(options, secret) — creates + HMAC-SHA256 signs a PactMandate
- verifyMandate(header, amountUsdc, secret) — verifies a mandate header (mirrors pact-verify.ts logic)
- encodeMandateHeader(mandate) — JSON.stringify for X-Pact-Mandate header
- Full TypeScript types: PactMandate, MandateScope, PactIssueOptions, PactVerifyResult
- Zero external dependencies (Node built-in crypto only)

